additional_house_rules:
Government issued I.D is required

No smokingNot suitable for pets

No parties or events

Not suitable for infants (Under 2 years)

Check-in time is 3PM - 2AM (next day).

Please don't remove or borrow anything from the apartment.

Always lock exterior doors behind you

Conserve energy - turn off lights, air conditioning etc...when not in use and when when you leave the house (thanks!)

Let us know how you're doing!

Please do not move the furniture for any reason.

Please do not put wet towels or clothes on the furniture.

Please lock the door when you leave.

Turn OFF all lights and appliances when not in use. Go Green!

Use of CANDLES and other COMBUSTIBLES are not permitted.

No Smoking!

No Parties!

DO NOT flush anything except toilet paper down the toilet.
There is a waste paper basket in the bathroom to dispose of napkins, paper towels, wet wipes, sanitary napkins, tampons, and dental floss.

LAUNDRY
There is NO washing machine or dryer on premises. Please do not do laundry on the premises. There is a laundromat on the corner and detergent in the apartment under the sink.

Guests are OK, with a HEADS UP. Your guests must be people you KNOW and TRUST. You are responsible for the actions of your guests. You are responsible for a fee if your guests spend the night.

Quiet time is in effect after 11 pm on weekdays and 1am on weekends.

FAILURE TO ABIDE BY ANY OF THE ABOVE RULES MAY RESULT IN YOU BEING ASKED TO LEAVE. THIS HAS NEVER HAPPENED BEFORE. DON'T BE THAT GUY/GAL.

Thanks!
description:
This beautiful spacious two bedroom apartment is located just 15 mins from JFK, 20 mins from Barclays center. Minutes away from Manhattan & Brooklyn bridge. 1 BLOCK AWAY from New York's main subway line. Entertainment, shopping & transportation are endless. This property has two bedrooms a sofabed in the living room & can accommodate up to 6 guests

Unique large two bedroom Apartment with large Queen bed & full size bed in separate bedroom.  Bright and sunny space with separate kitchen fully equipped. Great for large groups or a family getaway. Located 1 block away from the C train that can get you to and from the city in minutes.

Wifi, AC units, street parking, Roku TV

Guests can reach me anytime. I live close by so can be available within minutes.

We are located on a main road in a residential neighborhood that mostly has small 1-2 family homes. There's a laundromat on the same block, as well as a Supermarket across the street just 2 blocks away but best of all is the Spanish Cafe located to the right of the property at the end of the block, serving empanadas, chicken rice and more.

Located 1 block from the C train minutes to Manhattan and downtown Brooklyn. Located right off of major highway, 15 minutes from JFK and 25 minutes from LGA and 1 hour plus from Newark airport.

The C train is located just 1 block away from the house.

Subway Transit times are below using the C train:
15 Mins to Downtown Brooklyn and Barclays stadium
20 mins to World Trade Center in Manhattan
25 to Union Square in Manhattan
30 mins 34th Street Macy's store in Manhattan
36 mins to Tim Sq 42nd Street in Manhattan
38 mins to Grand Central in Manhattan
38 Mins to Central Park in Manhattan

hosts.about:
I'm from England and my Wife is from NY by way of St Lucia. We've been living in Brooklyn since 2012 and love and enjoy all of NY and what our neighborhood has to offer. We have a beautiful daughter and enjoy having as much fun together as possible, traveling and experiencing new wonders. 

We look forward to hosting you and making your visit to Brooklyn, and all of NY the best it can be.

I live in Brooklyn New York with my wonderful husband and beautiful daughter. My husband is from London and I'm from St. Lucia but we call Brooklyn home. Love to travel so we know exactly what's needed to make your stay fabulous and comfortable.

review.comments: Nous avons apprécié la communication facile avec les hôtes et le fait que la porte se verrouille à l'aide d'un code et non d'une clé. Le logement était confortable et propre. La station de métro qui vous amène à Manhattan est à seulement trois minutes de marche, ce qui est génial! Pour le côté négatif, la chambre principale donne sur une rue très bruyante et l'appartement n'est pas très isolé par rapport au voisins. Je vous conseille de vous apporter des bouchons.
